<p><%= SITE_NAME %> does not host course materials. Instead you will add course materials to, or reuse content from, <%= link_to "Connexions", "http://www.cnx.org" %> and <%= link_to "Quadbase", "http://www.quadbase.org" %>.</p>
    <p>
    You can assign two (2) kinds of material in <%= SITE_NAME %>: 
       <ol>
          <li> <em>Resources</em> from <%= link_to "Connexions", "http://www.cnx.org" %>: background material (text, tables, images, audio, video files etc).</li>
          <li> <em>Exercises</em> from <%= link_to "Quadbase", "http://www.quadbase.org" %>: free-form, multiple choice and true/false questions.</li>
       </ol>
       <p>
      Content in Connexions and Quadbase is open and free to use or reuse. Similarly, content you add to Connexions and Quadbase is easily shared -- allowing others to use and reuse it legally -- while still giving you recognition and attribution for your work.</li>
